            &lt;div class=&quot;comment-body js-comment-edit-hide&quot;&gt;

                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-copy&quot;&gt;@James: The value of a comma operation will always be the value of the last expression.  At no point will &lt;code&gt;i&lt;/code&gt; have the values 5, 4, 3, 2 or 1.  It is simply 0.  It&apos;s practically useless unless the expressions have side effects.&lt;/span&gt;

              &lt;div class=&quot;d-inline-flex ai-center&quot;&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;/users/390278/jeff-mercado&quot; title=&quot;122,425 reputation&quot; class=&quot;comment-user&quot;&gt;Jeff Mercado&lt;/a&gt;
                &lt;/div&gt;
                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-date&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;&lt;a class=&quot;comment-link&quot; href=&quot;#comment4504905_52558&quot;&gt;&lt;span title=&quot;2010-11-13 07:06:09Z, License: CC BY-SA 2.5&quot; class=&quot;relativetime-clean&quot;&gt;Nov 13, 2010 at 7:06&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
                        &lt;span title=&quot;this comment was edited 1 time&quot;&gt;
                            &lt;svg aria-hidden=&quot;true&quot; class=&quot;va-text-bottom o50 svg-icon iconPencilSm&quot; width=&quot;14&quot; height=&quot;14&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 14 14&quot;&gt;&lt;path d=&quot;m11.1 1.71 1.13 1.12c.2.2.2.51 0 .71L11.1 4.7 9.21 2.86l1.17-1.15c.2-.2.51-.2.71 0ZM2 10.12l6.37-6.43 1.88 1.88L3.88 12H2v-1.88Z&quot;&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;
                        &lt;/span&gt;
            &lt;/div&gt;

            &lt;div class=&quot;comment-body js-comment-edit-hide&quot;&gt;

                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-copy&quot;&gt;Note that there is a full sequence point between the evaluation of the LHS of the comma expression and the evaluation of the RHS (see &lt;a href=&quot;http://stackoverflow.com/users/1708801/shafik-yaghmour&quot;&gt;Shafik Yaghmour&lt;/a&gt;&apos;s &lt;a href=&quot;http://stackoverflow.com/a/18444099/15168&quot;&gt;answer&lt;/a&gt; for a quote from the C99 standard).  This is an important property of the comma operator.&lt;/span&gt;

              &lt;div class=&quot;d-inline-flex ai-center&quot;&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;/users/15168/jonathan-leffler&quot; title=&quot;700,796 reputation&quot; class=&quot;comment-user&quot;&gt;Jonathan Leffler&lt;/a&gt;
                &lt;/div&gt;
                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-date&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;&lt;a class=&quot;comment-link&quot; href=&quot;#comment37619769_52558&quot;&gt;&lt;span title=&quot;2014-06-20 20:47:15Z, License: CC BY-SA 3.0&quot; class=&quot;relativetime-clean&quot;&gt;Jun 20, 2014 at 20:47&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
                        &lt;span title=&quot;this comment was edited 1 time&quot;&gt;
                            &lt;svg aria-hidden=&quot;true&quot; class=&quot;va-text-bottom o50 svg-icon iconPencilSm&quot; width=&quot;14&quot; height=&quot;14&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 14 14&quot;&gt;&lt;path d=&quot;m11.1 1.71 1.13 1.12c.2.2.2.51 0 .71L11.1 4.7 9.21 2.86l1.17-1.15c.2-.2.51-.2.71 0ZM2 10.12l6.37-6.43 1.88 1.88L3.88 12H2v-1.88Z&quot;&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;
                        &lt;/span&gt;
            &lt;/div&gt;

            &lt;div class=&quot;comment-body js-comment-edit-hide&quot;&gt;

                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-copy&quot;&gt;&lt;code&gt;i = b, c;&lt;/code&gt; is equivalent to &lt;code&gt;(i = b), c&lt;/code&gt; because because assignment &lt;code&gt;=&lt;/code&gt; has higher precedence than the comma operator &lt;code&gt;,&lt;/code&gt;. The comma operator has the lowest precedence of all.&lt;/span&gt;

              &lt;div class=&quot;d-inline-flex ai-center&quot;&gt;
